content: Miaomiao Liu | ANU School of Computing School Sharepoint College Sharepoint ANU College of Systems & Society Search this site Search this site (powered by Google) Powered by Google Close search Research 3D Vision, 3D scene understanding and modeling, 3D human pose Estimation/Prediction, geometry-aware representation for 3D Vision. Biography I am currently a Senior Lecturer (Tenure-Track) and ARC DECRA Fellow in the School of Computing, ANU. I was a Research Scientist in Data 61, CSIRO, Canberra (2016-2018). Before that, I was a post-doc researcher working with Prof. Richard Hartley(2012-2014) and researcher in NICTA(2014-2016). I got my Ph.d degree in Nov. 2012 from the Department of Computer Science, the University of Hong Kong under the supervision of A/Prof. Kwan-Yee Kenneth Wong. bars search times
